text: Sepidan County () is a county in Fars Province in Iran. The capital of the county is Ardakan.Gitashenasi Province Atlas of Iranاطلس گیتاشناسی استان‌های ایران At the 2006 census, the county's population was 87,801, in 20,127 families. The county is subdivided into three districts: the Central District, Beyza District, and Hamaijan District. The county has three cities: Beyza, Hamashahr, and Ardakan. == References == == Other websites == Category:Sepidan County
